description:
&lt;p&gt;The diagnostics team has been expanded and further developed to drive the diagnostics agenda across the region through the fostering of effective relationships with both providers, commissioners and systems. The immediate aims of the team is to improve patient access and the quality of care to support both COVID-19 recovery and the delivery of key medium to long term objectives aligned to regional and national priorities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The purpose of the Head of Diagnostic Recovery (Pathology) is to deliver the pathology recovery agenda in response to:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;The requirements of the NHSE/I Phase 3 Recovery Programme:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Postholder will oversee the delivery of requirements for pathology services outlined within the NHS Long Term Plan &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Lead the delivery of pathology recommendations identified in ‘State of the nation’&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Ensure Diagnostic (pathology) proposals are reflected and owned by STPs and Providers in their 5 year plans including the movement of diagnostics in to primary care (LHCR). The Postholder will provide the regional leadership for ICS/STP pathology capital wave investment planning &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Postholder will actively work with others in the Diagnostic and Regional team ensuring effective use of resources and clear, consistent communication with internal and external stakeholders&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is offered as a fixed term appointment because of short-term time limited project. Those expressing interest should be available to commence in November 2020 and have the support of their employer for a six-month secondment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: h.crick@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
